    "narrative": "The Austin Waves open today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our premier offensive catalyst, boasting a robust score of 81.88. Batting leadoff against Lugo, the combination of a favorable wind and an advantageous platoon split makes him our highest-upside asset, despite a slight deduction for the opposing pitcher's elite holding ability on the basepaths. Following closely is **Andy Pages** (74.43), who benefits from a prime matchup against a struggling lefty in Quintana and park factors that inflate his power ceiling. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) also project as high-efficiency starts, with both players drawing favorable matchups against Elder and Irvin, respectively. The alignment of these top-tier bats against starters with xERAs near or above 4.50 provides the offensive density needed to climb the 5x5 standings today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's roster card involved the utility spot, where **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (55.26) narrowly edged out **Nolan Schanuel** (46.58). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces a challenging matchup against an elite arm in Detmers, his superior xwOBA profile and established order position at #3 ultimately outweighed **Nolan Schanuel**, who, despite a cleaner matchup against Cease, lacks the raw, high-leverage production potential in the current batting order. Elsewhere, we are exercising caution with **Josh Lowe** (53.53) and **Liam Hicks** (53.92); both are startable but sit near the threshold of our marginal range due to **Josh Lowe** facing the high-strikeout threat of Cease and **Liam Hicks** working in a less-than-ideal lineup slot. We continue to monitor the bench status of **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill**, all of whom are unavailable today, leaving us to rely on the current depth of **Dominic Smith** and **Jacob Wilson** to anchor the lower half of the order.",
